definition: abbr. for 克羅地亞|克罗地亚[Ke4 luo2 di4 ya4], Croatia/(Tw) abbr. for 克羅埃西亞|克罗埃西亚[Ke4 luo2 ai1 xi1 ya4], Croatia

sentences.english: The Bells of Bow Church spoke truly when they chimed to young Dick.
sentences.chinese: 當年包教堂的鐘聲對年輕的迪克的確說了真話。

sentences.english: Dick found himself walking in the direction of the church.
sentences.chinese: 迪克發現自己不知不覺朝教堂方向走去。

sentences.english: Dick fell for baseball when he was a little boy.
sentences.chinese: 當迪克還是個小孩時，他就迷戀上了棒球運動。

sentences.english: I beat Dick in billiards because he gave me tremendous odds.
sentences.chinese: 打彈子球我贏了迪克，因爲他讓了我很多。

sentences.english: Bill grudged Dick his prize even though he had won a better prize himself.
sentences.chinese: 比爾妒忌迪克獲獎，儘管他自己獲得了更高的榮譽。

sentences.english: Fred is much tall than dick.

sentences.chinese: 你喜歡迪克西蘭爵士樂嗎？

sentences.english: Taylor looked daggers at Atticus, as if daring him to speak.
sentences.chinese: 泰勒法官對阿迪克斯怒目而視，似乎看他敢不敢說話。

sentences.english: Mardy says Roddick's career will sit on his 15 times over .
sentences.chinese: 馬迪說羅迪克的職業賽生涯仍然讓他望塵莫及。

sentences.english: Dick took the pitcher and went to the ale-house.
sentences.chinese: 迪克拿着水罐去了啤酒店。

sentences.english: John's chance of being elected chairman of the committee is far greater than Dick .
sentences.chinese: 約翰當選爲委員會主席的可能性比迪克大得多。

sentences.english: Dixieland jazz is red hot and popular with many people.
sentences.chinese: 迪克西蘭爵士樂是非常受歡迎的火爆音樂。

sentences.english: My husband, Dick, and I asked Dad to come live with us on our small farm.
sentences.chinese: 我和丈夫迪克讓爸爸搬來我們的小農場，一起生活。

sentences.english: Dick and Fred are so much alike that it is impossible to know one from the other.
sentences.chinese: 迪克和弗雷德長得太像了，兩人分不清誰是誰。

sentences.english: Mr. Dick Bruna is one of the Netherlands' most celebrated artists.
sentences.chinese: 迪克布魯納先生是荷蘭著名的藝術家之一。

sentences.english: The next day, usman follow YiMing attended the wedding of SaDiKe.
sentences.chinese: 第二天，烏斯曼跟着伊明參加了薩迪克的婚禮。

definition: Clark T. Randt Jr. (1945-), US ambassador to Beijing 2001-2009
